re keys due to people having them that weren't returned to guilds when they left guilds, etc. (again because no warning... thanks)<br><br>you have accomplished what will probably only make negative competition for ST keys. unless a rotation is agreed upon, Reso and FnF are going to be racing to Zlandicar to get keys, and i'm sure ill feelings will ensue if there's no rotation. other options for keys are very limited. Plenty of people in each of the 2 guilds that can do ST already have Primal weapons and the other drops as well. and they are all droppable. really, what did you accomplish but instill negative competition? nothing. if you wanted to have the keys be no drop, then ya shoulda made them that way in the BEGINNING. <br><br>thank you so much Verant. you love your customers dont you? the VERY least you could have done is tell us in advance so we could retain more than half our keys. We still earned those keys.  what were you afraid of? that with warning, we'd all camp in ST before patch? do you think we're really THAT stupid? If we wiped out that would be a near impossible CR with alot of risk to losing our corpses. <br><br>as if you hadn't done enough for us, you go and do this shit. honestly if EQ weren't so addictive and more like a real business, you would have lost alot of your customers pulling that shit. if you dont understand anything else, maybe you'll understand what a bad business move is. oh wait... you're verant... nevermind.<br><br>EDIT: not to mention the myriad bugs brought on by this treachery. everytime someone puts a normally no drop(on regular servers) item in a trade window, their computer freezes. One would almost think this was intentional after the shit you just pulled. except for the fact that TLC + no drop makes absolutely no sense. And did you purposefully make some of the coldain shawls and rings(rumored) no drop? so what are people supposed to do about all the TLC quest pieces? dumbasses <p><BR><B>Baroness Veloxia Voluptuous </B><BR>57 Halfling Warrior~run speed 3~regen 3<BR>"Even the smallest person can change the course of the future" ~ Gandalf<BR>Veloxia@hotmail.com<BR><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~2emiller/Sig4final.jpg"></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uveloxiavoluptuous.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Veloxia Voluptuous</A> at: 6/6/02 3:29:41 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukarleafv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KarleaFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/6/02 6:15:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=779.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: a love letter to Verant(i know you guys read this board)</span><hr size=1> I think they made them no drop cause they want to avoid that 6 people go to e.g. Sebilis with only 3 actually having keys.<br><br>And I lost an hour of gaming due to my computer freezing 3 times during trades. Thanks a lot. <p><html><body><p align="center"><i><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=215107"><font color="#000000" size="3">Champion of the 51st scale.</font></a></b></i></p><p align="center"><i><b><a href="http://pub64.ezboard.com/bpropheticalliance"><font color="#000000" size="3">Proud member of the PropheticAlliance.</font></a></b></i></p></body></html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzarsissrazorscale.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zarsiss Razorscale</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/6/02 8:37:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=779.topic&index