s get going, let a nice rotation system get going, then dash it to pieces without warning. because they didn't warn us we lost keys too. we still earned those keys no matter what. we should still get to use them. all they have accomplished by doing this is to almost certainly promote negative competition(ya know FnF and Reso are actually getting along fairly well right now). who knows what will happen with both scrambling to take out the keyholders.<br><br> <p><BR><B>Baroness Veloxia Voluptuous </B><BR>57 Halfling Warrior~run speed 3~regen 3<BR>"Even the smallest person can change the course of the future" ~ Gandalf<BR>Veloxia@hotmail.com<BR><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~2emiller/Sig4final.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzarsissrazorscale.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zarsiss Razorscale</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/6/02 12:06:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=779.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: a love letter to Verant(i know you guys read this board)</span><hr size=1> Well no, I didn't miss the minor point, I just didn't address it. Because it wasn't done from the beginning doesn't make it right from the beginning. When our Lead GM saw that entry to ST was being trivialized, some sort of immediate action would obviously have been better than to allow an influx of unearned uber loot and then simply shut the valve later. It was a disservice to us all to consider something was wrong and not do something about it at the start. Maybe there was some deliberation to do in regards. Fixxing it, however late, was still the appropriate action. Announcing it might have been appropriate, but if you follow the tone of some of the discussions on these boards you might consider that option dangerous. Waking the sleeper might seem attractive to someone who is suddenly faced with months of work to do for something they've taken for granted all this time. While I'm sure more loot would be desired, a we have enough arguement could possibly be made. No offense intended anyone there, but it's something I would have considered were I representing VI's and FV's interest. At any rate, was even a single key lost? If so, is that such a big deal considering the fair effort it now takes to regain entry? <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=49821" target="_new">Zarsiss Razorscale</a><BR>Iksar Monk, 56th Scale<BR><a href="http://pub5.ezboard.com/bdreadstorm" target="_new">Dreadstorm</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umorgauth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Morgauth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/6/02 12:14:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=779.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/classes/c_necromancer.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: a love letter to Verant(i know you guys read this board)</span><hr size=1> in my 3 years of EQ ive seen verant treat us progressively worse, dont expect it to improve..... <p><img src=http://pic3.picturetrail.com/VOL22/566694/847606/10005863.ptp.gif ></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufeneant.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feneant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I got more post<br>than all of you</span><br>  Posts: 786<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/6/02 1:09:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffiri