ll around for more people to have the opportunity to see more zones before EQ's 'end of days', but that's not in the cards anymore. That seems a shame to me, but that's just my opinion.<br><br>Changes like this, long after they should have been changed if they were to be changed at all, are inherently bad in that the server is no longer a land of equal opportunity. Whatever detrimental effect they may have foreseen for the keys being tradeable, the eradication of equal opportunity for all players and all guilds overshadows it in my book.<br><br>Coriolis, Sage of Erudin, Phantasmist, Firiona Vie<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukzanverto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kzan Verto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Giver of da juice (tm)</span><br>  Posts: 575<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/8/02 7:19:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=779.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: a love letter to Verant(i know you guys read this board)</span><hr size=1> Nahide,<br><br>We have never had a problem with other folks going after monsters or exloring other zones. ST will be no different.<br><br>Reso and FnF have fought amongst themselves in the past. That was actually a misunderstanding,  what was perceived as a broken promise. But thats water under the bridge.<br><br>We have no interest in enforcing our ideals onto anyone on this server. We dont expect anyone to look up to us as rolemodels or as an example of &quot;how to do things&quot; (like when alignment was dropped and people were so curious as to how we would react).  All we want to do is play this game, take on new challenges and have some fun doing it. We would /cheer any guild who got to enter ST and infact I did just that when reso went in for thier first time. The only &quot;personal playground&quot; FnF has is our guildchat and raid channel.<br><br>ST was a thrill. Wether or not Verant wanted to allow players to enter that zone so early was discussed by folks in FnF and I am sure folks in Reso had similar conversations. But since they made the keys tradable, we assumed this was part of the FV rule set. Just like the seb keys, HS keys and having to deal with TLC.<br><br>GM's watched us in ST and cheered us on. We had no reason to believe that the key being tradable was not what Verant had intended. We certainly didnt consider it an exploit especially with GM's there congratulating us. The fact that they changed this on us with out warning is just poor planning on Verants part. If they meant the key to be no drop then they should have made it no drop to begin with. If this was an oversight on there part it seems only fair for them to warn us before they change it.<br><br>Edit: Cori is right. All this change has done is made it harder for other folks to get to see ST. FnF and Reso had enough Keys to do ST (obviously) and were just getting more keys as it was convienent. Now there will almost certainly be a &quot;lock&quot; on the monsters that will let folks get keys for ST for the next few months. Hopefully, by the time another guild is ready to try ST, Reso and FnF will have thier keys and wont need these monsters anymore.<br><br><br> <p>Kzan Verto<BR>Giver of "da juice" (tm)<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=220314" target="new">My Magelo Profile</a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukzanverto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kzan Verto</A> at: 6/8/02 7:31:08 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showMessageRange?topicID=779.topic&start=21&stop=35>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffi